{"nodes": [{"id": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase7_readme", "label": "phase7/ README \u2014 the readout: the GD namer on the frozen bulk", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\papers\\phase7\\README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Stage-2, first GD phase: the cold-start surprise is that because the bulk is frozen-to-GD, the namer's learning is (near-)convex \u2014 the scary 'now we need gradient descent' turns out small. Two hedges: convex names the regression not the deployed cost; reservoir-like but not a reservoir proper."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase7_convex_frame", "label": "Frozen-bulk readout is (near-)convex", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\papers\\phase7\\README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A trained readout on a fixed nonlinear bulk is reservoir-like: the regression has no bad local minima, needs no exotic optimizer \u2014 but the deployed softmax/normalizer/tap-reading is a real, non-free digital cost, measured by the Phase-8 cost meter."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase7_spine_cosine_only", "label": "Spine: only the cosine classifier is direction-pure", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\papers\\phase7\\README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "NCM/Deep-SLDA classify by distance to a class mean \u2014 a distance is a magnitude (SLDA with tied covariance is algebraically a linear-softmax with a ||mu||^2-scaled per-class bias); they are recency-robust, not the same as reading direction. The Phase-7 bake-off scores which readout stays spine-clean while matching prototype recency-robustness."}], "edges": [{"source": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase1_2_scff_gap_reason_for_gd", "target": "draft6_